How Do You Traverse Through a Dictionary Object in Python?

A dictionary can be traversed using a for loop along with methods like 
.keys() to access keys only,
.values() to access values only, or
.items() to access keys & values both.

eg:- dictionary={
    'name':'Aastha',
    'age':21,
    'course':DS
    }

To access keys only ---
    for k in dictionary.keys():
        print(k)

To access values only ---
    for v in dictionary.values():
        print(v)

To access both keys & values only ---
    for k,v in dictionary.items():
        print(k,v)